04:33.060 --> 04:41.580
times. It's very hard to follow because of the convoluted plot structure, the traveling through

04:41.580 --> 04:47.100
this time gate that allows him to emerge at various points in time. But it's still considered,

04:47.100 --> 04:53.740
as I said, a classic by some people. And Heinlein has used what has been termed cyclic time travel

04:53.740 --> 04:59.200
before, or at least he has used it since in other stories. This story, along with some of his other

04:59.200 --> 05:08.840
earlier ones, are based on a gimmick of some kind. Another one along these same lines, using an idea

05:08.840 --> 05:15.360
or a gimmick in it, is, and he built a cricket house. It's a very unusual and humorous short story

05:16.040 --> 05:23.240
concerning a fellow who builds a house in the form of an unfolded tesseract, or hypercube,

05:23.360 --> 05:29.940
a four-dimensional cube. This is a house that looks like four cubes stacked on top of each other with

05:29.940 --> 05:36.540
a cross cube on the second level up from the top. And he builds this thing in California,

05:37.000 --> 05:40.800
and there happens to be an earthquake one night, and the whole thing folds up. And now he has a

05:40.800 --> 05:45.180
four-dimensional house. When they enter it to find out what happened to the rest of the house,

05:45.600 --> 05:50.260
they aren't sure they think maybe someone came and took it away or something. They don't find any

05:50.260 --> 05:55.780
debris around it, however. But they go inside and look around and go up to where they think the

05:55.780 --> 06:00.580
roof is going to be, and it's another room. And they keep going up and up and up, and we get the

06:00.580 --> 06:05.580
top room and go up on what was the roof. They're back in the bottom room again. As they open windows

06:05.580 --> 06:12.680
