Yeah, the protagonist of that book Michael Valentine Smith, he's called a Martian but he's

25:22.500 --> 25:28.080
really a human that's grown up on Mars, he's never known the earth, his parents have gone to Mars,

25:28.240 --> 25:33.220
the ship had not come back, they died, he'd been born right before they died on the planet Mars

25:33.860 --> 25:39.960
and he comes back to earth I think in his mid-twenties and he's been raised by the Martians, the old

25:39.960 --> 25:46.740
ones I believe they're called and he's got some extremely strange powers which illustrate Heinlein's

25:46.740 --> 25:56.060
occasional interest in a sort of a superman type, a superhuman type, a special leader with powers

25:56.060 --> 26:01.500
and insights and wisdom that the common people don't have and the novel is based upon the

26:01.500 --> 26:08.540
strange powers of this Michael Valentine Smith. The story starts off as an action adventure story

26:08.540 --> 26:13.640
where Michael Valentine Smith is rescued from the hospital in which he's recuperating from the

26:13.640 --> 26:23.500
flight back to earth, he's taken to his soon-to-be father figure Jubal Hershaw and Jubal sets about

26:23.500 --> 26:29.600
and educating Michael in the ways and customs of earth. What Heinlein does in that book is

26:30.360 --> 26:35.360
Michael Smith or Michael Valentine Smith becomes educated in earth ways, it gives Heinlein the

26:35.360 --> 26:42.000
opportunity to view earth, its institutions, its customs and so forth with the point of view of an

26:42.000 --> 26:47.960
outsider, you know even though Michael is a human being, he's a Martian, he's been raised by Martians

26:48.460 --> 26:55.440
so his responses to what he sees on earth, the social institutions, the religions and so forth

26:56.220 --> 27:01.700
form I think the center of the book and Michael soon gathers a group of people around him

27:02.240 --> 27:08.060
and they become his followers and I guess you'd start what he, I guess he starts what you'd call

27:08.060 --> 27:16.240
a religion based on on certain things that he has learned in his upbringing on Mars. He eventually

27:16.240 --> 27:24.400
teaches several of his followers how to also use these particular powers that he has and in order to

27:24.400 --> 27:31.060
use these abilities one has to grok or to know and completely holistically understand

27:31.920 --> 27:39.560
certain concepts about the universe and how it operates. This particular word grok was

27:40.240 --> 27:46.600
quite popular in the 60s, it became kind of a catch word for the people who had read the novel.

27:47.240 --> 27:51.420
Yeah that especially the character of Smith and the word grok and so forth

27:51.420 --> 27:55.600
sort of became the property of the so-called flower children, the hippies of the 60s.

27:55.860 --> 28:02.060
